We have presented preliminary evidence that the neurodevelopmental transcriptional regulator PAX6 interacts with HOMER3 , DNCL1 and TRIM11 .
We suggest that the interaction of PAX6 with HOMER3 and DNCL1 is a mechanism by which synaptic signalling could lead to regulated changes in gene expression in neurons .
